      <br>
      <button class="accordion">How To Create An Account</button>
      <div class="panel">
        <p>To create an account click in the "Sign-Up/Login" button and fill in the information required to
          get you started. First come up with a Username you will remember, add an existing email, and create
          a password that you will remember when wanting to login. 
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <button class="accordion">Did You Forget Your Password?</button>
      <div class="panel">
        <p>If you forgot your password, please go to the "Sign-Up/Login" button. Once your in the page, click on
          the "Forgot Password" link. Follow the following instructions to create a new password once you have 
          filled the requested information.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <button class="accordion">How To Search For Something In Particular?</button>
      <div class="panel">
        <p>If you are looking for a book, then go to the "Book" tab and once redirected to the page there will be a
          search filter. On the right side there should be a dropdown that allows you to search something in particular.
          For the book page, you can select "ebooks", "free-ebooks", "full", "paid-ebooks", and "partial". Once you have 
          selected one of the options, type in your search and press search to get your results.
        </p>
      </div>

      <script>
        var acc = document.getElementsByClassName("accordion");
        var i;
        
        for (i = 0; i < acc.length; i++) {
          acc[i].addEventListener("click", function() {
            this.classList.toggle("active");
            var panel = this.nextElementSibling;
            if (panel.style.display === "block") {
              panel.style.display = "none";
            } else {
              panel.style.display = "block";
            }
          });
        }
        </script>
  </body>
